AUDIO: 'Hello creators and creative friends. Welcome to the channel. Today we are going to talk about post transfer using Flex 2 client. If you have used Flex 2 client for a while, you probably know one common problem. Sometimes it can get body anatomy wrong. It may generate'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'strange limbs, incorrect body parts, or poses that do not look natural. That is why in my previous videos, I did not use it as a main model for tasks like post transfer. But recently, with the help of'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Laura, Flex 2 client can now transfer a pose from a reference image to the portrait you want to edit. Let me show you a few examples so you can see what I mean. There are three images on the screen. The two images on the left are'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'reference images. The first one is a full body image and we use it as a post transfer. The second one is a headshot and we use it as a face reference. With the workflow I will introduce in this'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video, we can transfer the pose from the full body image to the woman in the headshot. The image on the far right is the final result. You can also customize her clothes and the background by changing the prompts. Now, let\'s look at'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'another situation. Suppose you already have a portrait and you only want to change her pose. You want the new pose to look similar to the image on the left. This workflow can also do that. At the same time, it can keep the subject\'s'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'identity, face, and overall style. All right, I think you now understand what post transfer means. But if it\'s still not very clear, do not worry. Let\'s jump into ComfyUI and look at the'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'workflow I built. I will put the workflow link in the video description. You can download it for free. This workflow was built on RunningHub, which is a cloud platform for ComfyUI. If you want to learn more about RunningHub, I'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will also put the links in the description. This workflow can be divided into two stages. First, we start with a post reference image. However, Flex 2 client cannot use this image directly for clean post transfer. So,'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this node group converts the portrait into a mannequin image. This step removes the subject\'s style, clothes, background, and other details. What remains is mainly the post information.'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This gives Flux to Client much cleaner post reference to follow. Now, this mannequin image is used as the reference image in a node group below. The other reference image is the'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'headshot. With these two reference images, plus a prompt that describes the clothes and background, Flux to Client generates a new image. The new portrait takes the pose from the'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'first reference image. At the same time, it keeps the identity from the second reference image. You can see that the final pose is very close to the original pose. More importantly, there are no obvious anatomy errors. So, why did Flux'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to Client work better this time? The answer is the LoRA adapters I used. In the first stage, I added this LoRA. You can download it from Hugging Face, and I have put the link in the'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description. This LoRA can turn almost any human reference image into a faceless glossy mannequin. At the same time, it keeps the pose and the body proportions. From the sample images, you can see what it does. It replaces the'

[03:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'human identity with a faceless green mannequin, while keeping the same pose, limb positions, and proportions. Depending on your prompt, it can either preserve the background or clean it up.'

[03:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For this task, we do not want to keep the background from the pose reference image. So, first, I use this image remove BG node to remove the background. Then, in a prompt, I also include the words remove garments and remove shoes.'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, the output is only a mannequin without clothes and without the original background. In the node group below, I I another LoRA. This LoRA was trained by the same'

[03:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'author as the previous one. It was designed as a companion model for the mannequin Laura. Its job is to transfer mannequin pose reference onto a character subject. In the prompt, you need to include the trigger word'

